description: Recently sold: $300,000. This beautiful 1911-built two story is stylish, updated, and impeccably turned out, with an airy open layout on the main level and 3 bedrooms the spacious  upper level! Home boasts large rooms throughout: Enter through lovely screen porch that runs the width of the home, into a roomy foyer showcasing a pretty open staircase and access to all main floor rooms. Living room and dining room feature gleaming original hardwood, crown molding, plaster ceilings and a fresh modern palette and lighting. Expanded eat in kitchen is functional and modern, with peninsula, cherry cabinets, ample counter and floor space, and access from foyer, dining room, and back porch. Up the elegant staircase is a big landing leading to three bedrooms, all featuring gleaming hardwood, modern palettes and lighting, great natural light, and ample closets, and a full, updated bath. Unfinished lower level has laundry, plus plenty of room for storage and project, plus laundry. Add to this a big fully fenced back yard featuring paver patio and walkways, and a 2001-built 2 ½ car garage, all in this wonderful, walkable Northeast neighborhood just steps from Audubon Park, blocks from great shopping and dining, and minutes from both downtowns!

description: Recently sold: $292,500. This is the Northeast home you've been waiting for!
